# Privacy Policy — MeetMinder

**Last updated: April 2026**

## Overview

MeetMinder is a Chrome extension that connects to Google Calendar to show your upcoming meetings and help you join them quickly. This policy explains how the extension handles your data.

## Data Collected

MeetMinder stores the following data **locally in your browser only**:

- Your Google OAuth access token (used to authenticate API requests, expires automatically)
- A cache of today's calendar events (refreshed every 5 minutes, used to render the popup without repeated API calls)
- The next upcoming event, held temporarily to fire a desktop notification at the right time

No calendar event content is stored beyond the current session cache. All cached data is cleared when you sign out.

## Google API Access

MeetMinder requests read-only access to your Google Calendar (`calendar.readonly`). This is used solely to fetch today's events and display them in the popup. No calendar data is modified.

Calendar data is fetched directly from Google's API in your browser and is never transmitted to any third-party server.

## Data Storage

All data is stored using Chrome's `storage.local` API. It never leaves your browser and is not accessible to any website or third party.

## Data Sharing

No data is collected, transmitted, or shared with any external server, service, or third party beyond the Google Calendar API, which is accessed directly from your browser using your own OAuth credentials.

## Sign Out

You can sign out at any time using the Sign out button. This immediately clears your stored token and cached events from local storage.

## Permissions

- **identity** - used to handle the Google OAuth sign-in flow
- **storage** - used to cache events and save your auth token locally
- **alarms** - used to schedule background calendar refreshes and meeting notifications
- **notifications** - used to show a desktop reminder before your next meeting

